OL,3,CNigel Farage demands Reform be allowed
OL,4,Cto nominate peers to the House of Lords
OL,6,FIn 1999, prior to reforms, membership
OL,7,Fof the House of Lords sat at nearly
OL,8,F1,200. This fell to around 700 after
OL,9,Fthe removal of hereditary peers'
OL,10,Fautomatic right to sit and vote.
OL,12,FThe makeup of the House of Lords
OL,13,Fcurrently gives the Conservatives 285
OL,14,Fseats and Labour 209. The government
OL,15,Fhas however committed in its manifesto
OL,16,Fto reform the chamber with the
OL,17,Fultimate ambition of replacing it
OL,18,Faltogether.
